      • isAssignable

        public boolean isAssignable(Type aType)
        Description copied from interface: Interface
        Determines the assignability of an instance of the argument type to an instance of this type. This method is similar in purpose to Class.isAssignableFrom().

        The strictest form of assignability is an identity match (this == aType). All implementations must answer true for an identity match.

        Note that assignability might be determined through the uniform name or a portion thereof. For example, given types with names of "ns.acme.com/2015/ctx1/app.ui.Widget" and "ns.rrinc.net/2014/afw/app.ui.Widget", either may answer true or false based on the common path suffix. Also note there is no requirement that there be commonality in the two names. One system may simply map names, paths, etc. into its type system.

        Specified by:
        isAssignable in interface Interface
        Overrides:
        isAssignable in class IInterface
        Returns:
        true when aType is assignable to this.
